## 🚀 CI/CD Pipeline Status
[![Main Branch Pipeline](https://github.com/Malviya-Shashank/github-actions-capstone/actions/workflows/main-pipeline.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/Malviya-Shashank/github-actions-capstone/actions/workflows/main-pipeline.yml)

🔹 Pull Request Flow (CI)

PR Opened / Updated
        ↓
Reusable Build & Test Workflow
        ↓
Tests Passed ✅
        ↓
PR Status Updated


🔹 Main Branch Flow (CI/CD)

Code Merged to main
        ↓
Build & Test (Reusable Workflow)
        ↓
Docker Build & Push
        ↓
Deploy to Production (Manual Approval)
        ↓
Application Live 🚀


🔹 Monitoring Flow

Every 12 Hours (Cron Job)
        ↓
Pull Latest Docker Image
        ↓
Run Container
        ↓
Health Check (/health endpoint)
        ↓
PASS / FAIL Report
        ↓
Cleanup Container

## 🔮 Future Improvements

To make this pipeline production-grade, I would add:

### 🔔 Notifications
- Slack / Email alerts on failure & success
- Integration with monitoring tools

### 🌍 Multi-Environment Deployment
- Separate environments: dev, staging, production
- Environment-specific configs & approvals

### 🔄 Rollback Strategy
- Ability to rollback to previous stable Docker image
- Use version tagging (v1, v2, etc.)

### 🐳 Container Registry Upgrade
- Use AWS ECR instead of Docker Hub
- Better security & IAM integration

### ☸️ Kubernetes Deployment
- Deploy using Helm charts
- Add liveness & readiness probes

### 📊 Monitoring & Logging
- Prometheus + Grafana dashboards
- Centralized logging (ELK / CloudWatch)

### ⚡ Performance Optimization
- Cache dependencies in GitHub Actions
- Parallel job execution

### 🔐 Security Enhancements
- Image scanning (Trivy)
- Secrets management (Vault / AWS Secrets Manager)